content.title: RStudio - User Adoption Rate
content.layoutDescription: Split view with code editor and console output
content.visibleText:
# User Adoption Rate

This function will plot the R^2 generated whenever a calculation is performed by A.

```R
# Load necessary libraries
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

# Define the function
user_adoption_rate <- function(data) {
 # Calculate R^2
 rsquared <- summary(lm(log10(users) ~ date, data = data))$r.squared
 
 # Plot
 ggplot(data, aes(x = date, y = log10(users))) +
 geom_point() +
 geom_smooth(method = 'lm') +
 labs(title = 'User Adoption Rate', subtitle = 'Plot of R^2 over time')
}

# Example usage
example_data <- data.frame(
date = as.Date('2020-01-01') + 0:29,
users = round(runif(30, 100, 1000))
)
user_adoption_rate(example_data)
```
